Gemfibrozil-induced myopathy.
 Drug-induced myopathy has been reported with use of lovastatin, nicotinic acid, and clofibrate.
 A particularly severe form, often accompanied by rhabdomyolysis, has been reported with the use of lovastatin and gemfibrozil; however, as far as we know, no case has been documented with use of gemfibrozil alone.
 Herein, we report the first case (to our knowledge of gemfibrozil-induced myopathy, confirmed by drug rechallenge.
